<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="166" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d166fn1">Channel of transmission not
                                indicated.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-29">29 June,
                                1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>To President from <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval Person</gloss>
                            personal and secret. Number 336.<note n="2" xml:id="d166fn2">For the
                                paragraph omitted here, see <ref target="frus1943CairoTehran#pg_13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, The Conferences at
                                    Cairo and Tehran, 1943, p. 13</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>I should be very glad to arrange for a meeting between us and our staffs
                            about the end of August in Quebec which I am sure Mackenzie King would
                            welcome. Later on I will put the point to him.</p>
                        <p>Many thanks for your very full message.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>